<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-01T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-01T03:00:00-05:00" n="32" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d32">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3181</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Droppers</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-01T10:00:00+02:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 1, 1917, 10 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 2, 8.15
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>237. Greek Government announce concession of Entente that
                                indispensable victuals may be introduced pending the raising
                                blockade. Entente allege large store rifles not yet accounted for.
                                Salute to flags Monday last.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_DG1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Droppers</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>[See telegram No. 4994, February 4, 1917 (received February 5,
                                    8.30 p.m.), from the Ambassador in Germany, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_114">page 114</ref>, for the
                                    following statement of peace terms reported as made to the
                                    Ambassador by the Chancellor: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                        <p>Germany to give up Belgium but retaining so-called
                                            guaranties such as railroads, forts, a garrison, ports,
                                            commercial control, etc.; a <pb facs="0210" n="38" xml:id="pg_38"/> slice of France through
                                            rectification of frontier; will only give back a small
                                            part of Serbia, and Bulgaria can do as she likes with
                                            Roumania and everybody must pay indemnities to Germany,
                                            etc.</p>
                                    </quote>
                                </p>
                                <p>The Ambassador adds: “If <persName corresp="#p_BJHC1">Bernstorff</persName> has given President any other terms
                                    he is fooling him, but do not quote me to <persName corresp="#p_BJHC1">Bernstorff</persName>.”]</p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>